or burning during urination. If a serious infection, an opportunistic infection, or sepsis develops, tofacitinib should be interrupted until the infection is controlled.', 'Others', 'Apremilast, Pirfenidone, Belumosudil, Teprotumumab, Dimethyl fumarate, Ravulizumab, Pegcetacoplan, Eculizumab, Sutimlimab', 'Apremilast, Pirfenidone, Belumosudil, Teprotumumab, Emapalumab, Baricitinib, Tofacitinib, Ravulizumab, Pegcetacoplan, Eculizumab, Sutimlimab', 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/87290/', '[1] "Product Information. Xeljanz (tofacitinib)." Pfizer U.S. Pharmaceuticals Group, New York, NY.', 1767369485);
